Your code doesn&#39;t execute the that mono, i.e., there is no subscription to it. 
Your `user` Mono kept untouched. 

You just create an object that could be called, never call it, and then return always 200 response that doesn&#39;t take into account any real work.

The code should look like:

    return user.map(result -&gt; {
        new ResponseEntity(result, HttpStatus.OK)
    });


Which means _subscribe to user mono and then provide with the following result_.

You may also want to handle errors and other situations, like:


    return user
        .map(result -&gt; {
            new ResponseEntity(result, HttpStatus.OK)
        })
        .onErrorResume(t -&gt; {
            new ResponseEntity(null, HttpStatus.INTERNAL_ERROR)
        })
        .switchIfEmpty(new ResponseEntity(null, HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND);

You need a subscriber to user [Mono][1] and add chain of actions using [map][2] for success response, and on error you can use [onErrorResume][3] to return `ResponseEntity` with appropriate status code

    return user.map(data -&gt; {
              //log the data if needed
              return new ResponseEntity(data, HttpStatus.OK)
              }).onErrorResume(throwable -&gt; {
                     log.error(&quot;Failed for some reason&quot;, throwable));
                     return new ResponseEntity(null, HttpStatus.INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR);
                   });


  [1]: https://projectreactor.io/docs/core/release/api/reactor/core/publisher/Mono.html
  [2]: https://projectreactor.io/docs/core/release/api/reactor/core/publisher/Mono.html#map-java.util.function.Function-
