answers.body_markdown:
## The problem you are experiencing

Note that you have nested loops.
```java
do{
    while(CardDealt &lt;= numCards){
        //...
        response = scan.next().charAt(0);
    }
} while(response == &#39;Y&#39;); 
```

So, you are only looping until all cards are dealt and only then checking the response.

Instead, you can integrate the `CardDealt &lt;= numCards` check in the `do while`-loop:

```java
do{
    //...
    response = scan.next().charAt(0);
} while(response == &#39;Y&#39; &amp;&amp; CardDealt &lt;= numCards); 
```
This will check the response in each iteration and stop the loop if it isn&#39;t `Y`.

## Other issues/improvements

### re-creating `Scanner`
Also, I would not recommend you to create a new `Scanner` in each iteration. Instead, you can reuse the same scanner throughout your whole program:
```java
